  "prompt": "What are the functions of knee pads?",
  "response": "Knee pads serve several important functions:\n\n1. Protection\n- Cushion the knee from direct impacts\n- Prevent cuts, scrapes, and bruises\n- Shield against hard surfaces and sharp objects\n\n2. Safety\n- Reduce risk of knee injuries\n- Provide support during high-impact activities\n- Minimize potential damage during falls or accidents\n\n3. Professional Use\n- Essential for construction workers\n- Used by flooring installers\n- Helpful for mechanics and technicians\n- Important for painters and tile workers\n\n4. Sports and Recreation\n- Protect athletes during contact sports\n- Used in skateboarding, rollerblading, and cycling\n- Provide cushioning during volleyball, wrestling, and other activities\n\n5. Comfort\n- Reduce strain on knee joints\n- Minimize pain during kneeling activities\n- Provide padding for prolonged kneeling\n\n6. Performance Enhancement\n- Improve stability\n- Help maintain proper posture\n- Reduce fatigue during extended periods of kneeling\n\n7. Medical Support\n- Assist individuals with weak or injured knees\n- Help prevent further knee joint damage\n- Provide compression and support during rehabilitation\n\nKnee pads are versatile protective gear designed to enhance safety and comfort across various professional and recreational activities.",
